The I/O adapter in slot 2 is reporting an internal hardware error.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Ensure the interconnects are powered-on and otherwise functioning correctly. Perform following actions only when the drive enclosure is not in use by server profiles. Shutdown all server profiles using this drive enclosure. Hard reset the drive enclosure.   If the problem persists reset the associated interconnects.     If the problem continues, re-seat the contained I/O adapters, and finally re-seat the drive enclosure.  If the problem cannot be resolved, contact your authorized support representative and provide them with a support dump.

members.description: Link errors have been detected on port 2 and it is operating in a degraded performance state.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Power off any affected server profiles. Perform a hard reset of the interconnect. If problem persists, incrementally replace the hardware until the problem goes away. First try replacing the IO adapter in slot 2 of {"name":"CZJ9260730, bay 7","uri":"/rest/drive-enclosures/CN700310NX"}. If problem persists, try replacing the SAS connection module. If problem persists, try replacing the chassis of {"name":"CZJ9260730, bay 7","uri":"/rest/drive-enclosures/CN700310NX"}. If problem persists, try replacing the midplane of {"name":"CZJ9260730","uri":"/rest/enclosures/797740CZJ9260730"}. If the problem still persists, contact your authorized support representative and provide them with a support dump.

The logical interconnect can be made consistent with its logical interconnect group via update from group. The logical interconnect or group may also be edited to manually restore consistency.
